                            <comment id="12740976" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Sat, 8 Aug 2009 22:32:42 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching quick hack of a patch to handle the situation the same as ord()... via top() to pop back to the top level reader.  This isn&apos;t so bad since scale() was never really production quality anyway, since it doesn&apos;t cache the min and max -recomputing it each time.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12740977" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Sat, 8 Aug 2009 22:35:17 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed, and moving remainder of the work (per-segment fieldcache usage, caching min+max) to 1.5&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
